{
  "texts": [
    "We adopt EvalRepair-Java [102] as the evaluation benchmark on federated fine-tuning.",
    "EvalRepair-Java consists of 163 code samples and is built on top of the foundation of HumanEval-Java [115], which was widely used and specifically designed to avoid data leakage by excluding itself from the pre-training datasets of existing LLMs.",
    "EvalRepair-Java provides enhanced test cases that more accurately reflect the performance of the fine-tuned LLMs.",
    "By integrating additional test cases from EvalPlus [55], EvalRepair-Java significantly increases the average number of test cases per problem from 7 to 583.",
    "This substantial expansion of test cases plays a vital role in mitigating the risk of patch overfitting caused by a limited number of test cases during the evaluation process."
  ]
}